definition.value: An L-alpha-amino acid anion arsing from deprotonation of the carboxy and phosphate OH groups of 4-phospho-L-aspartic acid.
An iron-sulfur cluster is a unit comprising two or more iron atoms and bridging sulfur ligands.
A  molybdenum coordination entity consisting of a {Mo:7Fe:9S:C]:homocitrate cluster, having carbide(4-) at its centre. Active site of the enzyme nitrogenase (EC 1.18.6.1).
A cobalt-corrinoid hexaamide that is cobalamin with the oxidation state of the central cobalt atom unspecified.
A heme is any tetrapyrrolic chelate of iron.
An organotin compound carrying four methyl groups.
A metallic element first identified and named from the brilliant indigo (Latin indicum) blue line in its flame spectrum.

Dextroamphetamine in which the the hydrogens attached to the amino group are substituted by a methyl and a benzyl group. A sympathomimetic agent with properties similar to dextroamphetamine, it is used as its hydrochloride salt in the treatment of obesity.
A metallic element first identified and named from the brilliant green line in its flame spectrum (from Greek thetaalphalambdalambdaomicronsigma, a green shoot).
